headline.main: Interesting from Calcutta.; THE AMERICAN MAIL MISSING--RISING OF THE GANGES--EXPORTS OF MERCHANDISE TO THE UNITED STATES--THE MARKET FOR AMERICAN GOODS--FREIGHAS--SCHUYLERISM IN THE BANK OF BENGAL--THE STEAM TUG ASSOCIATION--COLLIFS--SENDING A LOBBY MAN FROM INDIA TO THE BRITISH PARLIAMENT--NEW PORT REGULATION.

docs.lead_paragraph: On Tuesday of last week the English mail steamer Bontinek, Capt. FARQUTAR, arrived at town from Suez 23d alt., and Madras 11th inst. By her we have received files of the NEW-YORK DAILY TIMES up to the 23d of July, and English papers up to the 10th of August. The balk of the American mail was not brought by the steamer.
